default? 
defaultIf the total contribution from the 
defaultGovernment
default to the sector is increasing, that gives us more confidence that it is safe for us to increase
default. 
defaultAt the end of the day, you are right; you can never prove perfectly the counterfactual
default. 
defaultWe do have a long track record of paying a lot of attention to levels of military expenditure, for example, and saying to countries we think there should be limits
default. 
defaultThe 2% figure has been used internationally for a long time and this is a big part of the dialogue
