default. 
defaultI wonder if you can tell us to what degree you think this is actually happening and what controls are in place to ensure that teams do not contract out those services simply to avoid operating costs.
defaultMark defaultLowcockdefault: The controls are basically about the rules that apply to the administration budget and the operating cost budget, on the one hand, and the programme budget on the other hand
default. 
defaultWe have not had significant problems with breach of those rules
default. 
defaultI do not think it is a major problem in practice; it is one that conceptually could arise
default.
defaultAs you know, we have had a substantial growth in the professional capability of the Department over the last three years
default. 
defaultStaffing levels have gone to roughly 3,000 from 2,500 or so in 2010
default. 
defaultWe needed to do that because we were planning to deliver a lot more
default. 
